# skills_sbin contains tracked OS skills AND machine-local symlinks to user
# skills in $HORIZON_USRBIN/usr_skills (created by horizon_aios_register_user_skills.py).
# git traverses Windows symlinks, so without this whitelist those user skills
# would be staged into the OS repo. Ignore everything, then re-include each
# tracked OS skill. When adding a new OS skill here, add it to this whitelist
# (skill-creation enforces this in the same commit).
*
!.gitignore
!index.md
!handoff/
!handoff/**
!objective/
!objective/**
!skill-creation/
!skill-creation/**
!model-prefs/
!model-prefs/**
!resync-user-skills/
!resync-user-skills/**
!horizon_aios_dev_consistency_check/
!horizon_aios_dev_consistency_check/**
!horizon_aios_documentation_index_update/
!horizon_aios_documentation_index_update/**
!harden/
!harden/**
!create-brain/
!create-brain/**
!remove-brain/
!remove-brain/**
!pre-flight-tooling-validation/
!pre-flight-tooling-validation/**
!model-prefs-assign/
!model-prefs-assign/**
!agent-teams/
!agent-teams/**
!horizon_aios_wiki_upkeep/
!horizon_aios_wiki_upkeep/**
!horizon_aios_wiki_update/
!horizon_aios_wiki_update/**
!terseness-check/
!terseness-check/**
!test-agent-teams/
!test-agent-teams/**
!convert-prompt-to-saill/
!convert-prompt-to-saill/**
!doc-check/
!doc-check/**
!post-update/
!post-update/**
